sentences: Bjarne Bent Rønne Pedersen, known as Bjarne Liller (25 September 1935 – 6 September 1993), was a Danish jazz musician and singer-songwriter.
He played with the Viking Jazz Band from 1956–70, and again from 1976-79, and made around 30 records with the band.
Liller credited Kim Larsen and Erik Clausen for re-igniting his passion for music during the last years of his life.
A sold-out benefit concert was held by his former jazz colleagues at the Tivoli Gardens later that month.
